WEBVTT

00:50.254 --> 00:53.966
PERFECT CROWN

01:04.851 --> 01:06.060
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

01:06.061 --> 01:07.980
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

01:21.618 --> 01:23.579
All rise
for His Majesty the King!

02:11.251 --> 02:13.378
Let us begin the discussion on abolishing…

02:15.255 --> 02:16.256
the monarchy.

02:27.184 --> 02:30.479
PERFECT CROWN

02:38.487 --> 02:39.946
So… No, no.

02:49.998 --> 02:52.375
He should have told them by now, right?

02:52.376 --> 02:53.459
Yes, he should have.

02:53.460 --> 02:56.504
The court historians
must've recorded it by now, right?

02:56.505 --> 02:58.923
Once it's in the records,
it's set in stone.

02:58.924 --> 03:00.132
We're in trouble now.

03:00.133 --> 03:02.843
This won't do. I'll call Hyejeong…
I mean, Aide Do--

03:02.844 --> 03:03.845
Just shush!

03:11.269 --> 03:14.398
Tomorrow, you'll be His Majesty,
and not His Royal Highness.

03:15.941 --> 03:17.566
You'll also be Queen tomorrow,

03:17.567 --> 03:18.777
and not the Grand Princess.

03:20.821 --> 03:22.614
What will you record first in the Annals?

03:26.326 --> 03:29.286
On the day the newly crowned king
first enters the Throne Hall,

03:29.287 --> 03:32.457
all are assembled,
from the Cabinet to the royal family.

03:33.166 --> 03:35.502
Like a traditional ceremony of sorts?

03:36.420 --> 03:38.088
With all the court historians too.

03:39.047 --> 03:40.131
Yeah.

03:40.132 --> 03:42.467
I didn't even know this was a big deal.

03:43.093 --> 03:44.510
I've seen so many gatherings.

03:46.972 --> 03:49.641
That's because we caused them
a great deal of trouble.

03:53.687 --> 03:54.688
So?

03:55.772 --> 03:57.858
What will be
your first proclamation as King?
:cue

04:09.244 --> 04:10.829
Words that…

04:14.583 --> 04:15.834
carry great weight.

04:20.589 --> 04:22.048
The backlash could be severe.

04:24.634 --> 04:26.052
But still, I'm sure you…

04:27.137 --> 04:28.472
I will understand you.

04:37.981 --> 04:39.357
I'm going to abolish the Crown.

04:43.528 --> 04:44.738
Inherited titles and status

04:45.405 --> 04:46.948
can become a privilege

04:47.949 --> 04:48.950
or a constraint.

04:51.828 --> 04:53.079
It all stems from the Crown.

05:00.879 --> 05:02.547
I thought it was treason.

05:06.134 --> 05:07.469
Turns out it was a revolution.

05:08.887 --> 05:09.888
Your dream.

05:23.568 --> 05:24.986
You've just attained this title.

05:25.821 --> 05:27.571
Are you ready to let it go?

05:27.572 --> 05:31.409
I never said I wanted status.

05:32.869 --> 05:35.330
I was just pissed off
about the opportunities it cost me.

05:41.044 --> 05:42.254
That's when I knew.

05:44.047 --> 05:45.048
That you'd be…

05:46.591 --> 05:47.592
my revolution.

06:06.611 --> 06:07.779
Your Majesty.

06:08.363 --> 06:09.822
Abolition of the monarchy?

06:09.823 --> 06:11.366
You cannot mean what you say.

06:11.867 --> 06:14.660
Every year, most nations
with constitutional monarchies

06:14.661 --> 06:16.787
revisit the question
of their own abolition.

06:16.788 --> 06:18.706
But that is…

06:18.707 --> 06:20.166
Prime Minister Min.

06:20.876 --> 06:21.959
Yes, Your Majesty.

06:21.960 --> 06:23.795
What about our country?

06:24.379 --> 06:28.257
We conduct formal opinion polls,
but opposition remains high every year.

06:28.258 --> 06:30.260
I believe the divide is not so vast.

06:31.970 --> 06:33.346
For a decade now,

06:34.097 --> 06:35.848
that gap has steadily narrowed.

06:35.849 --> 06:38.602
The Crown does not exist
to prove its worth.

06:40.687 --> 06:43.315
Its value lies in its very existence.

06:51.323 --> 06:54.284
"We do not need a king
who lacks the people's support."

06:55.410 --> 06:56.828
I believe those were your words.

06:59.831 --> 07:00.832
Have you forgotten?

07:13.887 --> 07:15.347
Kings may come and go…

07:21.186 --> 07:22.687
but the Crown endures.

07:29.027 --> 07:31.195
You're saying the Cabinet
and Royal Relatives

07:31.196 --> 07:33.073
will oppose it, no question?

07:33.698 --> 07:34.948
Yes.

07:34.949 --> 07:38.410
Most of the establishment
is connected to the Crown.

07:38.411 --> 07:41.580
The monarchy and the political world
have always sustained each other.

07:41.581 --> 07:43.667
The Royal Relatives go without saying.

07:45.877 --> 07:47.629
So His Majesty has nothing to rely on

07:48.838 --> 07:50.382
but public sentiment.
:cue

07:55.011 --> 07:56.470
- There he is!
- He's here!

07:59.933 --> 08:02.184
Is it true there are talks
of abolishing the monarchy?

08:02.185 --> 08:03.895
Is this your first time hearing about it?

08:09.275 --> 08:10.943
The people of this nation

08:10.944 --> 08:13.196
have nothing to worry about.

08:14.197 --> 08:16.115
Please say more!

08:16.116 --> 08:17.616
One more statement, please!

08:21.287 --> 08:24.289
The release
of the 34th monarch's first agenda

08:24.290 --> 08:26.458
has triggered a major stir.

08:26.459 --> 08:30.045
This agenda starts the discussion
on the abolition of the monarchy.

08:30.046 --> 08:32.464
As Prime Minister Min left the palace,

08:32.465 --> 08:34.091
he reassured the public…

08:34.092 --> 08:35.551
He just ascended the throne.

08:35.552 --> 08:37.553
Why would he abolish the monarchy?

08:37.554 --> 08:38.637
I know, right?

08:38.638 --> 08:40.849
Do you think Father knows about this?

08:41.474 --> 08:42.851
Damn it…

09:22.348 --> 09:24.934
How dare you show your face here?

09:27.854 --> 09:29.606
I wanted to see for myself

09:30.899 --> 09:32.775
the gravity of the sins I have committed.

09:32.776 --> 09:35.695
Do you even realize what you have done?

09:37.072 --> 09:40.033
I'm asking if it feels good
to cast aside your own father and son.

09:42.118 --> 09:44.412
Have you no pity for that poor boy,

09:45.789 --> 09:49.459
now cast into the shadows
like some relic of a bygone age?

09:51.878 --> 09:53.004
That poor boy…

09:56.049 --> 09:57.425
knew everything all along.

10:00.053 --> 10:02.222
He knew the full measure of my sins,

10:03.932 --> 10:06.434
and he silently shouldered
that heavy burden.

10:07.018 --> 10:08.185
What are you saying?

10:08.186 --> 10:10.021
Do you know how I felt

10:11.189 --> 10:13.691
when I learned of your sins?

10:17.737 --> 10:19.614
When you so proudly claimed

10:20.907 --> 10:22.450
that it was all for my sake.

10:24.702 --> 10:27.914
Do you know how that made me feel?

10:35.088 --> 10:36.089
So…

10:38.133 --> 10:40.135
may this mark the end of your sins.

10:41.886 --> 10:43.054
From this day forth…

10:47.058 --> 10:48.476
you have no daughter to claim.

11:02.657 --> 11:03.700
Your Majesty!

11:06.995 --> 11:08.621
Prime Minister Min, that bastard…

11:19.883 --> 11:21.718
He knew about the explosion

11:22.719 --> 11:25.471
when he drew
the Grand Prince to that place.

11:27.974 --> 11:30.602
You must stop either
the Grand Prince or His Majesty.

11:31.936 --> 11:33.104
Do whatever you must.

12:13.937 --> 12:14.938
Let me escort you

12:15.939 --> 12:17.523
back to the palace.

12:27.075 --> 12:29.994
MY SON
:cue

12:40.380 --> 12:41.463
There he is.

12:41.464 --> 12:42.547
Father.

12:42.548 --> 12:45.884
Is it true what they're saying
about abolishing the monarchy?

12:45.885 --> 12:47.302
- They're not, right?
- Are they?

12:47.303 --> 12:49.096
How can they abolish the Crown?

12:49.097 --> 12:50.890
Father, say something.

12:53.518 --> 12:55.936
My brother-in-law just
became King.

12:55.937 --> 12:58.230
How can they abolish it already?

12:58.231 --> 13:00.065
- "Brother-in-law"?
- Why? What's wrong?

13:00.066 --> 13:01.900
He is my brother-in-law, right?

13:01.901 --> 13:03.403
Address him properly.

13:03.945 --> 13:05.904
You don't want to get people talking.

13:05.905 --> 13:07.281
Let's not kid ourselves.

13:07.282 --> 13:09.491
There's no title to speak of
if there's no Crown.

13:09.492 --> 13:11.868
You just became Lord JUNGHWA.
You're finally a lord--

13:11.869 --> 13:12.954
Taeju!

13:18.710 --> 13:20.503
For the time being,

13:21.921 --> 13:23.006
watch your backs.

13:25.049 --> 13:26.133
Our backs?

13:26.134 --> 13:29.136
Why would you say
something like that, Father?

13:29.137 --> 13:30.179
You're scaring me.

13:34.183 --> 13:35.184
Wait…

13:41.774 --> 13:44.819
There will be another discussion
on the monarchy's abolition next week.

13:45.695 --> 13:48.406
His Majesty will seek to leave
that decision to the people.

13:49.198 --> 13:50.450
The Cabinet will oppose it.

13:51.534 --> 13:54.454
I'll need you
to voice your objection there.

14:00.460 --> 14:02.170
I am powerless.

14:04.756 --> 14:06.382
I'm not asking you to exercise power.

14:07.175 --> 14:09.259
Simply hint that the abolition
of the monarchy

14:09.260 --> 14:13.097
is His Majesty's own pursuit,
not the will of the Crown.

14:13.848 --> 14:14.932
And if I refuse?

14:16.434 --> 14:18.144
What will happen then?

14:23.691 --> 14:26.611
Do you wish to see your only son
follow in your father's footsteps…

14:29.322 --> 14:30.823
and be branded a criminal as well?

14:44.587 --> 14:45.797
Your Majesty.

14:47.548 --> 14:49.341
Prime Minister Min is not holding back.

14:49.342 --> 14:51.427
The palace budget has been put on hold.

14:57.308 --> 15:00.477
I knew he'd try to rein us in,
but I expected a different approach.

15:00.478 --> 15:02.521
Snipping the purse strings was a low blow.

15:02.522 --> 15:04.689
This will immobilize
the Queen's Quarters first.

15:04.690 --> 15:07.026
The royal finances are
under the Queen's jurisdiction.

15:07.652 --> 15:10.446
She just became Queen
and is already set to come under fire.

15:10.947 --> 15:12.323
What's the most pressing issue?

15:12.907 --> 15:14.325
The palace attendants' salaries.

15:14.867 --> 15:16.869
The Royal Guard
and administrative officials…

15:17.954 --> 15:18.955
:cue

15:19.664 --> 15:20.665
Excuse me.

15:21.791 --> 15:22.959
I'm Seong Huiju.

15:23.584 --> 15:25.335
The only money problems I've had were,

15:25.336 --> 15:27.963
"Gosh, how am I ever going
to spend all this money?"

15:27.964 --> 15:29.297
That's it.

15:29.298 --> 15:31.383
So what? Will you donate to the Crown?

15:31.384 --> 15:32.884
Yeah.

15:32.885 --> 15:34.137
What?

15:34.846 --> 15:38.223
What's the point of having wealthy in-laws
if you can't make use of them?

15:38.224 --> 15:41.059
- Let me see. How short is the budget?
- Well, this is…

15:41.060 --> 15:43.521
I appreciate the sentiment, but no.

15:44.021 --> 15:45.730
We need to think long-term.

15:45.731 --> 15:48.191
We can't think long-term right now.

15:48.192 --> 15:49.735
I already told you.

15:50.236 --> 15:52.362
When you pursue
a venture everyone opposes,

15:52.363 --> 15:54.699
you can't give them the time to object.

15:59.412 --> 16:01.247
PRIME MINISTER MIN JEONGWOO

16:01.873 --> 16:04.875
The Crown must've been up in arms.
Thank you for handling that.

16:04.876 --> 16:06.169
Actually, sir…

16:12.008 --> 16:15.136
The palace turned down funding
for the second half of the year.

16:17.430 --> 16:19.431
But they won't
be able to operate without it.

16:19.432 --> 16:21.850
Castle Group has made
a donation to the Crown.

16:21.851 --> 16:24.604
The amount they received
exceeds their annual budget.

16:32.028 --> 16:33.988
Look at His Majesty
making use of his in-laws.

16:35.364 --> 16:36.365
How petty.

16:41.495 --> 16:43.496
GREMLIN

16:50.671 --> 16:51.838
Hey, Dayeong.

16:51.839 --> 16:53.299
I'm a bit busy right now.

17:03.392 --> 17:05.603
What's going on? What summons?

17:07.396 --> 17:08.898
Is this intel from your family?

17:09.815 --> 17:10.899
Yes.

17:10.900 --> 17:12.776
It's a slush fund probe.

17:12.777 --> 17:16.113
They say a formal summons
will be issued within a day or two…

17:19.617 --> 17:20.618
This is clearly

17:21.869 --> 17:23.370
a direct attack on me.

17:23.371 --> 17:25.330
If you know that, don't play into it.

17:25.331 --> 17:26.332
I won't.

17:27.375 --> 17:29.502
It's a threat to deter us
from funding the Crown.

17:30.962 --> 17:32.838
Why give them the satisfaction?

17:37.134 --> 17:38.219
What's with that face?

17:39.303 --> 17:40.387
Dayeong.

17:40.388 --> 17:42.722
Can you check
who is leading the investigation?

17:42.723 --> 17:44.183
Why do you ask?

17:44.934 --> 17:46.477
I'm going to change the narrative.

17:47.061 --> 17:48.104
From slush funds

17:49.272 --> 17:50.439
to abuse of power.

17:56.404 --> 17:57.572
Well, in that case…

17:58.239 --> 17:59.782
I'll go in for questioning, Father.

18:00.324 --> 18:03.201
Are you nuts? Why would you do that?

18:03.202 --> 18:05.495
Father's blood pressure
has been acting up and all.

18:05.496 --> 18:08.582
The stress from all the questioning
might just push him over the edge.

18:08.583 --> 18:13.421
And it's only right for the successor
to handle these matters.

18:14.088 --> 18:16.548
- Babe, are you still drunk?
- Don't be absurd--

18:16.549 --> 18:18.175
Go ahead then.

18:19.176 --> 18:20.553
What?

18:22.054 --> 18:25.348
A bit of media exposure
wouldn't be the worst thing.

18:25.349 --> 18:26.767
Father.

18:27.435 --> 18:28.560
Is that all, Father?

18:28.561 --> 18:31.855
I've actually been meaning
to say this for a while now.

18:31.856 --> 18:34.983
Right now, I'm offering
to take your place in the investigation,

18:34.984 --> 18:36.318
out of pure filial devotion.

18:36.319 --> 18:39.321
I'm not asking
for tears of gratitude, am I?

18:39.322 --> 18:40.655
But maybe a little praise?

18:40.656 --> 18:41.991
Or at least a warm…

18:42.867 --> 18:43.909
What? Too far?

18:45.620 --> 18:46.703
I'm off.

18:46.704 --> 18:47.705
Wait.

18:48.664 --> 18:51.000
Don't just sit there.
Escort her back to the palace.

18:51.584 --> 18:52.877
Me? Escort who?

18:53.628 --> 18:54.629
Her?

19:01.719 --> 19:03.095
You shouldn't be out alone.

19:19.195 --> 19:20.404
What? What now?

19:20.988 --> 19:24.282
Castle Beauty's legal team
is highly capable.

19:24.283 --> 19:25.618
What?

19:26.744 --> 19:28.079
Let me know if you need help.

19:32.541 --> 19:33.625
You worried about me?

19:33.626 --> 19:35.336
You must be insane.

19:36.629 --> 19:38.129
That's not it.

19:38.130 --> 19:39.840
You're going in Father's place.

19:40.341 --> 19:41.550
So do it right.

19:42.259 --> 19:43.636
Don't give them any ammunition.

19:45.805 --> 19:48.391
Hey, I have years of experience
as a wealthy heir too.

19:49.392 --> 19:51.142
You're the only one who belittles me.

19:51.143 --> 19:52.186
Just you.

19:54.438 --> 19:55.856
I'll try to be less harsh now.

19:56.941 --> 19:58.150
Brother.

20:00.486 --> 20:01.487
"Brother"?

20:04.448 --> 20:06.617
Wait, what are you going to do?

20:07.368 --> 20:08.451
What was it?

20:08.452 --> 20:09.536
You're doing what now?

20:09.537 --> 20:11.497
:cue

20:16.711 --> 20:19.088
"I'll try to be less harsh now."

20:20.005 --> 20:23.134
No way.

20:25.678 --> 20:28.639
Your Majesty,
the Queen has arrived.

20:29.140 --> 20:30.599
Show her in.

20:38.065 --> 20:39.108
What's wrong?

20:39.692 --> 20:41.277
I'm exhausted.

20:50.369 --> 20:52.079
I went to see Father today.

20:53.998 --> 20:54.999
Your father?

20:55.833 --> 20:56.876
Nobody told me that.

20:57.460 --> 20:59.502
I slipped out alone
without telling anyone,

20:59.503 --> 21:01.255
so don't give Aide Choi a hard time.

21:03.549 --> 21:04.550
You went alone?

21:05.176 --> 21:06.594
I had no other choice.

21:07.428 --> 21:08.721
I was feeling too restless.

21:10.890 --> 21:11.932
Why?

21:19.482 --> 21:20.733
As early as tomorrow,

21:21.525 --> 21:23.694
prosecutors will begin
investigating Castle Group.

21:26.989 --> 21:28.282
Hold on. Get up--

21:31.744 --> 21:33.996
Father told me
not to play into their hands.

21:35.623 --> 21:39.877
Seong Taeju volunteered for questioning
with his chest all puffed up.

21:41.462 --> 21:42.962
It was so annoying.

21:44.048 --> 21:46.174
Why couldn't they just get angry?

21:46.175 --> 21:47.593
That would've been less awkward.

21:50.888 --> 21:51.889
Seong Huiju.

21:54.850 --> 21:56.602
Then again, you know…

21:57.186 --> 21:59.396
I mean, like…

22:00.981 --> 22:02.191
I didn't exactly hate it.

22:05.027 --> 22:06.654
It felt a bit reassuring,

22:07.446 --> 22:08.948
in a way.

22:15.663 --> 22:17.331
You should do that for me too.

22:18.833 --> 22:20.251
You should hold your ground

22:21.126 --> 22:22.336
and puff out your chest,

22:23.170 --> 22:24.420
so I can feel reassured.

22:37.768 --> 22:38.769
I will.

22:43.607 --> 22:44.608
Do it again.

22:47.194 --> 22:48.612
- Super reassuring, right?
- Yeah.

23:02.710 --> 23:05.671
Do you wish to see your only
son follow in your father's footsteps…

23:07.298 --> 23:08.799
and be branded a criminal as well?

23:17.725 --> 23:19.226
What is that supposed to mean?

23:23.689 --> 23:25.523
I'm referring to three years ago,

23:25.524 --> 23:28.027
when you disposed
of the late King's royal edict.

23:35.784 --> 23:37.702
I do not know what you are talking about--

23:37.703 --> 23:40.998
If it's revealed you defied a royal decree
to seat your son upon the throne,

23:41.999 --> 23:43.083
the abdicated King

23:44.418 --> 23:46.503
will go down in history as a criminal.

23:49.256 --> 23:51.717
Not as a king or even a royal.

23:53.093 --> 23:54.178
Just a criminal.

23:57.598 --> 23:58.599
For eternity.

24:01.268 --> 24:02.645
How dare you…

24:07.399 --> 24:08.775
I've only kept my mouth shut

24:08.776 --> 24:10.986
because I was worried
the Crown would crumble.

24:13.781 --> 24:15.616
You worry that much about the Crown…

24:19.036 --> 24:20.829
yet you tried to kill I-AN?

24:31.423 --> 24:33.384
I am willing to do whatever it takes…

24:36.011 --> 24:37.554
as many times as necessary.

24:53.654 --> 24:55.114
How difficult it is…

24:57.449 --> 24:58.909
just to keep you safe.
:cue

25:09.628 --> 25:11.129
There he is!

25:22.808 --> 25:24.559
Is it true that Castle Group maintains

25:24.560 --> 25:26.728
a slush fund
in the hundreds of billions of won?

25:26.729 --> 25:29.022
Can you explain the donation
you made to the Crown?

25:29.023 --> 25:31.482
Has the Queen reached out to you at all?

25:31.483 --> 25:33.109
Let's all calm down first.

25:33.110 --> 25:35.571
- Castle Group's slush fund…
- Let me just say this first.

25:36.739 --> 25:40.450
Well, you know, the Crown and the Cabinet

25:40.451 --> 25:43.202
just happens to be clashing
at this moment.

25:43.203 --> 25:45.621
The timing of this
seems just perfect, doesn't it?

25:45.622 --> 25:47.207
But still,

25:47.791 --> 25:50.294
I pledge to fully cooperate
with the investigation.

26:05.893 --> 26:07.186
Do you have something to say?

26:09.313 --> 26:10.314
No, Your Majesty.

26:15.277 --> 26:16.403
What is it?

26:17.071 --> 26:20.449
Perhaps you'd like
to visit the Queen Mother's Quarters?

26:23.243 --> 26:26.955
I believe you should if you want
to persuade the Office of Royal Relatives.

26:31.376 --> 26:32.544
Let her rest.

26:35.464 --> 26:37.424
She has only just ended her battle.

26:46.266 --> 26:47.726
Can you imagine it?

26:50.646 --> 26:52.773
This nation without a monarchy.

26:54.149 --> 26:55.776
I am curious.

27:00.114 --> 27:01.823
Are you not afraid?

27:01.824 --> 27:04.952
Are you afraid, Mother?

27:25.013 --> 27:26.140
That's surprising.

27:27.349 --> 27:28.683
What is?

27:28.684 --> 27:31.562
I heard she's barely left
her quarters recently.

27:32.729 --> 27:33.730
Is that so?

27:34.273 --> 27:36.191
After what happened
with Lord INPYEONG,

27:36.692 --> 27:39.736
she probably finds it difficult
to face the court attendants right now.

27:51.123 --> 27:53.125
Are you asking me for help?

27:54.751 --> 27:55.752
Yes.

27:57.546 --> 27:58.755
The royal family

28:00.173 --> 28:01.884
still listens to what you have to say.

28:04.177 --> 28:06.555
I had wondered why His Majesty
withheld his punishment.

28:09.266 --> 28:11.018
It appears he had his reasons.
:cue

28:37.502 --> 28:38.503
It is me.

28:45.427 --> 28:46.762
You made the right decision.

29:36.311 --> 29:38.605
I have reviewed
the petition you have submitted.

29:41.441 --> 29:42.900
The royal family called upon me

29:42.901 --> 29:45.070
to safeguard the realm and the dynasty.

29:46.822 --> 29:49.449
And the Cabinet implored me
to fulfill my duties as the King.

29:50.534 --> 29:52.577
Is that correct?

29:53.787 --> 29:56.539
We were simply speaking
on behalf of the public, Your Majesty.

29:56.540 --> 29:57.582
Did you bother to ask?

29:58.917 --> 29:59.960
It is my understanding…

30:01.712 --> 30:03.504
that the people were never surveyed.

30:05.090 --> 30:06.091
Your Majesty.

30:06.717 --> 30:08.844
- The Cabinet was chosen by the people--
- So?

30:09.428 --> 30:11.972
You intend to make every choice for them?

30:16.143 --> 30:17.394
"All people are equal."

30:18.478 --> 30:22.064
It is stipulated in our Constitution.
However, the existence of the Crown

30:22.065 --> 30:24.150
only serves to reinforce class divisions

30:24.151 --> 30:26.193
and undermine equality, does it not?

30:26.194 --> 30:27.319
Your Majesty, that is--

30:27.320 --> 30:28.989
Shielded by royal privileges,

30:30.365 --> 30:31.783
royal family members run amok,

30:33.702 --> 30:35.870
and the nobles aligned with them

30:35.871 --> 30:37.497
flaunt their power before the people.

30:38.290 --> 30:39.458
What do you think of this?

30:43.962 --> 30:45.255
What you seek to preserve

30:46.590 --> 30:47.632
is neither this kingdom

30:49.551 --> 30:50.594
nor the monarchy.

30:51.845 --> 30:53.597
It is merely your precious noble status.

31:01.188 --> 31:02.189
Your Majesty.

31:03.231 --> 31:06.943
Having lived a life sheltered by privilege
in an unequal world, you may not be aware.

31:07.486 --> 31:10.280
But the Crown's contribution
to the nation is not just financial.

31:10.947 --> 31:12.824
Economy, diplomacy, and culture.

31:13.325 --> 31:14.700
Its influence extends--

31:14.701 --> 31:16.078
So?

31:19.122 --> 31:20.706
Is that why you tried to kill him?

31:28.715 --> 31:31.093
Economy, diplomacy, and culture.

31:32.010 --> 31:35.262
Did the threat of abolishing
such an influential monarchy

31:35.263 --> 31:37.224
compel you to attempt to assassinate…

31:40.894 --> 31:42.437
the King of this nation?

31:43.396 --> 31:44.397
Seong Huiju.

31:47.275 --> 31:48.401
Your Majesty.
:cue

31:57.202 --> 31:58.994
RECORDING 1

31:58.995 --> 32:02.707
Do you wish to see your only
son follow in your father's footsteps…

32:03.208 --> 32:04.876
and be branded a criminal as well?

32:06.753 --> 32:08.421
What is that supposed to mean?

32:08.922 --> 32:10.756
I've only kept my mouth shut

32:10.757 --> 32:13.009
because I was worried
the Crown would crumble.

32:14.010 --> 32:16.262
You worry that much about the Crown,

32:16.263 --> 32:18.306
yet you tried to kill I-AN?

32:19.766 --> 32:22.144
I am willing to do
whatever it takes…

32:24.229 --> 32:25.897
as many times as necessary.

32:37.367 --> 32:39.035
The day I went to visit my father…

32:41.246 --> 32:42.664
Let me escort you

32:44.332 --> 32:45.875
back to the palace.

32:47.794 --> 32:49.462
MY SON

32:55.677 --> 32:58.555
This is what
Prime Minister Min had come to tell me.

33:04.603 --> 33:06.855
His Majesty cannot bring himself
to forsake mercy.

33:08.440 --> 33:10.483
However, you are different.

33:12.402 --> 33:13.987
When it comes to Prime Minister Min,

33:15.363 --> 33:16.698
no blow will cut deeper

33:17.699 --> 33:19.201
than one that comes from you.

33:41.806 --> 33:42.807
Is this…

33:44.601 --> 33:45.727
all true?

33:51.191 --> 33:52.776
Answer me!

33:53.610 --> 33:56.362
Your Majesty, perhaps we should
verify the facts first--

33:56.363 --> 33:57.572
I asked the prime minister.

33:58.156 --> 34:00.617
- Please excuse the royal family--
- From now on,

34:02.077 --> 34:03.787
anyone who defends the prime minister…

34:05.789 --> 34:07.082
shall be deemed an accomplice

34:08.708 --> 34:10.210
to the one who sought my life.

34:14.673 --> 34:16.549
Your Majesty.

34:50.041 --> 34:51.042
Your Majesty.

34:51.918 --> 34:52.919
Go…

34:54.504 --> 34:55.964
and protect His Majesty.

34:56.589 --> 34:57.674
Yes, Your Majesty.
:cue

35:30.415 --> 35:31.416
Jeongwoo.

35:39.007 --> 35:40.133
Did you really…

35:43.553 --> 35:44.554
try to…

35:48.141 --> 35:49.392
Try to kill you?

35:56.399 --> 35:57.400
Yeah.

36:11.414 --> 36:12.415
Why?

36:20.548 --> 36:21.633
I begged you.

36:26.429 --> 36:28.098
I begged you to push Huiju away.

36:30.141 --> 36:32.060
I told you I'd protect you if you did.

36:33.561 --> 36:34.688
Time and time again.

37:03.508 --> 37:04.551
It's your fault…

37:07.345 --> 37:08.471
I turned out this way.

37:28.658 --> 37:30.118
It's your fault for thinking…

37:36.332 --> 37:38.168
I took her when she was never yours.

38:43.900 --> 38:44.901
Are you okay?

38:47.737 --> 38:48.738
What about you?

39:02.168 --> 39:03.253
You did well.

39:17.267 --> 39:19.601
For the first time
in constitutional history,

39:19.602 --> 39:21.854
a nationwide referendum

39:21.855 --> 39:24.815
on the future of the monarchy
commenced at 8:00 a.m. today.

39:24.816 --> 39:27.317
This vote, which stands
to fundamentally reshape the relationship

39:27.318 --> 39:29.945
between the monarchy,
the government, and the people,
:cue

39:29.946 --> 39:34.157
is being widely regarded
as a defining moment for the nation.

39:34.158 --> 39:37.619
Following extensive negotiations,
the Crown and the government have agreed

39:37.620 --> 39:41.790
to put the question of abolishing
the monarchy to a public vote.

39:41.791 --> 39:43.625
Ultimately, His Majesty's principle

39:43.626 --> 39:47.588
that the people must decide
whether the monarchy is retained

39:47.589 --> 39:49.923
or abolished has prevailed.

39:53.386 --> 39:54.762
What would you want to do first

39:56.014 --> 39:57.181
if it passes?

39:58.558 --> 39:59.684
Hmm.

40:01.561 --> 40:02.562
My name.

40:03.313 --> 40:04.314
Your name?

40:05.273 --> 40:06.274
Do you know my name?

40:07.066 --> 40:10.612
You think I don't know
my own husband's name?

40:11.237 --> 40:12.322
You've never used it.

40:12.822 --> 40:14.282
That's because royals…

40:14.824 --> 40:15.825
Exactly.

40:17.452 --> 40:18.453
So…

40:19.954 --> 40:22.707
if it passes, I want you to call me…

40:24.125 --> 40:25.126
by my name.

40:28.671 --> 40:29.672
I will.

40:59.869 --> 41:01.037
It's the weekend.

41:03.373 --> 41:05.959
You should go
to the private residence and rest too.

41:07.043 --> 41:10.755
Well, I'm most at ease
at the palace.

41:16.386 --> 41:18.304
The thought of abolishing the monarchy

41:19.305 --> 41:20.848
must make you a little sad.

41:22.433 --> 41:23.434
Why?

41:26.729 --> 41:28.939
The palace is home to you.

41:30.942 --> 41:34.278
Come on. Your family doesn't change
just because you move.

41:34.862 --> 41:38.700
I'll still have
His Majesty and Her Majesty.

41:41.828 --> 41:42.829
And you

41:44.038 --> 41:47.166
will be there as well.

41:48.084 --> 41:49.085
Right?

41:58.261 --> 41:59.720
Hyeon, you have something here.

41:59.721 --> 42:00.930
Come closer.

42:10.231 --> 42:12.066
Why? Am I moving too fast? Bad idea?

42:16.821 --> 42:17.822
Good idea.

42:41.846 --> 42:43.931
Oh, my goodness.

42:46.309 --> 42:47.852
That's youth for you.

42:49.103 --> 42:50.646
My goodness.

42:52.648 --> 42:53.733
Let's go already!

43:06.079 --> 43:07.121
So cute.

43:17.715 --> 43:19.175
That hurts.

43:19.967 --> 43:21.052
How about

43:21.844 --> 43:22.845
when spring comes,

43:23.971 --> 43:25.598
we go see the cherry blossoms?

43:27.892 --> 43:28.893
Sounds good.

43:34.649 --> 43:35.774
You're so short.

43:35.775 --> 43:38.819
When we go see the cherry blossoms,
I'm going to lift you up

43:38.820 --> 43:41.863
and carry you around like this.

43:41.864 --> 43:43.198
Just like this.

43:43.199 --> 43:44.617
:cue

43:58.381 --> 44:00.298
Thus proclaims the King.

44:00.299 --> 44:02.093
THUS PROCLAIMS THE KING

44:03.177 --> 44:04.553
For many years,

44:04.554 --> 44:07.390
this nation has maintained stability
through the Crown.

44:09.016 --> 44:11.394
At times, it offered protection.

44:12.728 --> 44:13.729
At others,

44:14.522 --> 44:16.232
it hindered progress.

44:18.568 --> 44:23.239
The people have spoken and have decided
to bear full responsibility themselves.

44:24.282 --> 44:25.616
In light of their decision,

44:26.117 --> 44:27.118
the Crown

44:29.036 --> 44:30.830
can no longer claim justification.

44:31.414 --> 44:34.124
By the final authority

44:34.125 --> 44:36.002
vested in me by the Constitution,

44:37.170 --> 44:38.796
I hereby proclaim the abolition…

44:40.798 --> 44:41.799
of the monarchy.

44:44.886 --> 44:46.095
The 34th King,

44:47.263 --> 44:48.347
Lee Wan.

45:34.227 --> 45:35.603
Huiju!

45:42.818 --> 45:43.819
Wan!

45:47.323 --> 45:48.449
Lee Wan!

46:16.519 --> 46:17.728
- Let's go.
- Okay.

46:41.252 --> 46:45.589
THREE YEARS LATER

46:56.434 --> 46:57.518
Over here!

47:03.316 --> 47:04.941
It has been three years

47:04.942 --> 47:06.818
since Ms. Seong
left her company for the palace.

47:06.819 --> 47:09.237
She has now returned
to the board to resume

47:09.238 --> 47:11.073
a frontline management role.

47:15.828 --> 47:17.620
Industry insiders believe

47:17.621 --> 47:21.542
her return will significantly impact
Castle Group's succession dynamics.

47:22.043 --> 47:23.418
As the nation's last queen

47:23.419 --> 47:26.212
and a leading figure
in the abolition of the monarchy,

47:26.213 --> 47:30.800
there is growing interest in what changes
she will bring to Castle Group.

47:30.801 --> 47:32.177
CASTLE BEAUTY CEO SEONG HUIJU

47:32.178 --> 47:33.596
How have you been?

47:38.142 --> 47:39.310
I missed you so much.

47:39.935 --> 47:41.103
Are you really that happy?

47:46.192 --> 47:47.193
Move.

47:48.152 --> 47:49.153
:cue

47:55.618 --> 47:57.286
It has been far too long.

48:01.582 --> 48:04.877
Let's just say you've been on sabbatical.

48:05.378 --> 48:07.837
Don't you think I work too hard
abolishing the monarchy

48:07.838 --> 48:08.964
for it to count as one?

48:11.717 --> 48:12.802
What? Hold on.

48:13.552 --> 48:14.553
What is all this?

48:15.054 --> 48:17.472
Senior Managing Director
Seong's projects.

48:17.473 --> 48:19.391
You asked me to organize
all related files.

48:19.392 --> 48:20.643
Why are there so many?

48:21.227 --> 48:22.770
He worked on a ton of projects.

48:26.982 --> 48:28.109
What in the world?

48:30.653 --> 48:32.070
ADVERTISEMENT MODEL, SEONG TAEJU

48:32.071 --> 48:34.031
He made himself the face of the brand?

48:34.573 --> 48:37.701
Who in their right mind would buy this?

48:41.038 --> 48:42.832
- Hello, sir.
- Hi, Ms. Do.

48:43.582 --> 48:45.041
- Taeju.
- Yes?

48:45.042 --> 48:48.795
I'm currently reviewing
your project proposals, you see.

48:48.796 --> 48:51.047
- This is…
- No need to thank me.

48:51.048 --> 48:53.383
Can you just do me a favor?

48:53.384 --> 48:56.010
You're going to ask
for a favor too?

48:56.011 --> 48:58.681
I need you to manage Castle Card as well.

49:01.225 --> 49:02.226
What?

49:04.311 --> 49:06.897
Then, what will you be doing?

49:08.065 --> 49:09.941
Did Father ask you to go to Electronics?

49:09.942 --> 49:12.862
Don't kid yourself.
He's not retiring anytime soon.

49:15.698 --> 49:16.699
Then why?

49:18.534 --> 49:20.369
How do I say this?

49:21.370 --> 49:22.371
Listen.

49:22.913 --> 49:24.290
My Dayeong is pregnant.

49:26.584 --> 49:27.585
What?

49:28.294 --> 49:30.463
You're going to be an aunt, kid.

49:31.213 --> 49:33.299
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

49:34.008 --> 49:35.091
So?

49:35.092 --> 49:37.552
What do you mean?
I need to go on paternity leave.

49:37.553 --> 49:39.472
She can't do all that by herself.

49:44.143 --> 49:46.728
Have you lost your freaking mind?

49:46.729 --> 49:48.813
- Get back here!
- I'll take that as a yes!

49:48.814 --> 49:50.274
Thanks, I appreciate it!

50:02.077 --> 50:03.786
You should just give up on cooking.

50:03.787 --> 50:05.455
Clearly, this isn't your strong suit.

50:05.456 --> 50:07.708
Hey, like you were so great
from the start?

50:08.292 --> 50:09.667
Yes, I was actually.

50:09.668 --> 50:10.669
Really?

50:15.341 --> 50:16.342
By the way,

50:17.635 --> 50:19.428
when are you planning to go back to work?

50:21.639 --> 50:24.891
I mean, you set up a whole foundation
after sorting out the royal assets.

50:24.892 --> 50:27.019
Are you just never going to
show up for work?

50:28.312 --> 50:29.605
I just need a little longer.

50:31.357 --> 50:32.942
I used to work day and night.

50:33.776 --> 50:35.319
I can take a bit more time off.

50:36.320 --> 50:38.447
I can review the key documents from home.

50:39.823 --> 50:40.866
But you know,

50:41.617 --> 50:44.203
most women aren't into guys
who don't have a job.

50:45.120 --> 50:46.788
- Really?
- Of course.

50:46.789 --> 50:49.332
I mean, look at how hard your wife
is working at her job.

50:49.333 --> 50:50.334
While you…

50:51.794 --> 50:54.713
If you just bum around the house all day,
it's not a good look.

50:55.256 --> 50:57.507
Hey, I'm not "bumming around."

50:57.508 --> 50:58.591
I'm resting.

50:58.592 --> 51:00.719
That's the same difference… sir.

51:01.595 --> 51:03.596
Why, you…

51:03.597 --> 51:04.974
Unbelievable.

51:08.519 --> 51:09.520
Hey, Huiju.

51:10.145 --> 51:11.647
I'm cooking dinner.

51:12.940 --> 51:14.191
Are you on your way home?

51:15.067 --> 51:17.778
I don't think I can join you
for dinner today.

51:18.737 --> 51:20.781
Why not? Did something happen?

51:21.407 --> 51:23.075
No, it's nothing like that.

51:24.660 --> 51:26.536
I actually have another call coming in.

51:26.537 --> 51:28.913
Ms. Do won't be able to join you either.

51:28.914 --> 51:30.290
You two should eat without us.

51:30.291 --> 51:31.292
I have to go now.

51:31.875 --> 51:33.167
Wait. Hold on, babe.

51:33.168 --> 51:34.460
You're telling me this now?

51:34.461 --> 51:35.629
Hello? Babe?

51:37.172 --> 51:40.258
Why? Is she too busy for you?

51:40.259 --> 51:42.177
Yeah. Ms. Do also can't make it.

51:46.181 --> 51:47.850
I didn't see her yesterday either.

51:49.268 --> 51:50.269
I didn't either.

51:53.522 --> 51:54.857
:cue

51:57.318 --> 51:58.401
Hello there.

51:58.402 --> 52:00.403
I worked hard on that dinner.

52:00.404 --> 52:01.488
Why are we eating out?

52:02.072 --> 52:03.448
Wan, check your conscience.

52:03.449 --> 52:05.158
Who'd eat that? You want diabetes?

52:05.159 --> 52:07.201
- Why you little…
- Do you want to try that?

52:07.202 --> 52:08.287
- That one?
- Yeah.

52:12.541 --> 52:13.792
Mmm.

52:24.887 --> 52:26.262
What's with that face?

52:26.263 --> 52:27.347
What?

52:27.348 --> 52:29.641
It's nothing. I'm glad you're enjoying it.

52:29.642 --> 52:30.643
Is it tasty?

52:31.477 --> 52:32.602
It is.

52:33.771 --> 52:34.897
Hold on a second.

52:35.648 --> 52:37.190
That's new.

52:37.191 --> 52:39.025
It's nothing. Hyejeong kept saying

52:39.026 --> 52:41.736
she wanted this
to celebrate our third anniversary.

52:41.737 --> 52:43.155
You like it?

52:44.198 --> 52:45.406
It's not bad.

52:45.407 --> 52:47.993
- Wait, your third anniversary?
- Yeah.

52:49.453 --> 52:51.120
You guys should be hitting it soon.

52:51.121 --> 52:52.455
No, we're past that.

52:52.456 --> 52:53.499
When did you two start?

52:54.625 --> 52:55.917
Start?

52:55.918 --> 52:58.336
Come on. You know it was
all fake in the beginning.

52:58.337 --> 52:59.588
Watch it!

53:03.634 --> 53:05.009
It wasn't all fake.

53:05.010 --> 53:06.762
It wasn't all real, either.

53:11.600 --> 53:13.227
Maybe you can redo the proposal?

53:13.769 --> 53:14.770
Pro…

53:15.646 --> 53:17.522
- Proposal?
- Yeah.

53:17.523 --> 53:19.817
You don't even have
a wedding band.

53:25.656 --> 53:27.157
Proposal…

53:29.451 --> 53:31.411
Hello, Court Lady Choi. I mean, Jinsook.

53:31.412 --> 53:32.413
I'm listening.

53:34.373 --> 53:35.374
Wait, where are you?

53:41.505 --> 53:42.631
Come in.

53:48.929 --> 53:49.930
Father?

53:56.270 --> 53:57.813
I spoke with Taeju.

53:59.773 --> 54:01.024
Just prove yourself.

54:03.569 --> 54:05.696
I'll make sure the cards

54:06.447 --> 54:07.656
aren't stacked against you.

54:28.343 --> 54:29.344
Huiju.

54:32.723 --> 54:34.683
I never wanted you to lose.

54:36.185 --> 54:38.771
I just wanted you
to stop fighting everyone.

54:44.735 --> 54:45.736
Now…

54:47.905 --> 54:49.281
I won't stop you.

55:27.486 --> 55:28.737
Why would you

55:29.446 --> 55:30.613
gift us a bed?

55:32.366 --> 55:33.367
Just come.

55:34.451 --> 55:37.621
- Try sitting on it, Your Majesty.
- Stop calling me that already.

55:39.414 --> 55:40.415
:cue

55:42.626 --> 55:43.627
Here we go.

55:46.129 --> 55:47.130
A bed…

55:48.465 --> 55:50.592
It's quite soft.

55:54.096 --> 55:55.389
- Oh. Ooh.
- Ooh.

55:59.977 --> 56:01.395
Is it not comfortable?

56:03.397 --> 56:04.564
It is.

56:04.565 --> 56:06.816
I hear it will help you sleep very well.

56:06.817 --> 56:08.277
He sleeps fine now.

56:11.530 --> 56:13.991
It has been over three years
since your marriage,

56:14.700 --> 56:16.826
but there is still no news of an heir.

56:19.037 --> 56:22.665
I was hoping a precious bed
could lead to some precious news.

56:24.418 --> 56:25.543
Precious news.

56:25.544 --> 56:28.337
There will never be precious news.
They're both DINKs.

56:28.338 --> 56:30.464
- Choi Hyeon!
- DINK?

56:30.465 --> 56:33.843
Well, Huiju just started working again.

56:33.844 --> 56:34.927
And I…

56:34.928 --> 56:37.096
Is there something wrong with His Majesty?

56:37.097 --> 56:38.390
I said, I'm not a majesty!

56:39.641 --> 56:40.642
Follow me.

56:41.143 --> 56:42.978
No, wait… And also!

56:44.062 --> 56:45.397
I'm in tip-top shape!

56:59.911 --> 57:01.955
Oh, my gosh!

57:02.831 --> 57:04.041
You scared me.

57:05.584 --> 57:07.043
Why aren't you sleeping?

57:07.044 --> 57:08.545
My wife wasn't home.

57:09.171 --> 57:11.714
How could I, as your husband, just sleep?

57:13.842 --> 57:15.593
Sorry. You can go to bed now.

57:15.594 --> 57:16.637
Hold on.

57:19.181 --> 57:20.307
Did you need something?

57:21.516 --> 57:22.643
No, I…

57:24.853 --> 57:27.189
Seong Taeju told me
he's going to take some time off.

57:28.190 --> 57:29.566
I might be a bit busier now.

57:30.525 --> 57:31.609
All of a sudden? Why?

57:31.610 --> 57:33.362
He said Dayeong is pregnant.

57:34.196 --> 57:35.404
What?

57:35.405 --> 57:40.242
You know how professional executives
in this country are a dime a dozen?

57:40.243 --> 57:42.870
But he just had to…

57:42.871 --> 57:45.665
He just had to pick me

57:45.666 --> 57:47.917
and ask me to take over.

57:47.918 --> 57:50.587
Brother? More like a pain in the ass.

57:53.006 --> 57:54.007
You seem excited.

57:56.385 --> 58:00.013
Castle Card has
all the cash in Castle Group.

58:02.974 --> 58:03.975
I'm going to wash up.

58:29.084 --> 58:30.085
Should I get one?

58:31.420 --> 58:32.421
What?

58:34.548 --> 58:35.590
A ring.

58:36.842 --> 58:38.677
What ring?

58:39.511 --> 58:40.512
You know…

58:41.805 --> 58:43.265
Most husbands

58:44.015 --> 58:46.017
wear a wedding band.

58:46.643 --> 58:47.644
Well…

58:50.272 --> 58:51.605
Why bother?

58:51.606 --> 58:52.941
What?

58:56.778 --> 58:58.029
Why bother?

59:00.866 --> 59:01.867
Seong Huiju.

59:04.619 --> 59:05.620
Huiju.

59:07.998 --> 59:09.290
Babe.

59:09.291 --> 59:10.833
Ms. Seong. Ms. Junior Alum.

59:10.834 --> 59:12.377
Hello?

59:12.961 --> 59:13.962
Seong…

59:17.632 --> 59:18.633
You're asleep.
:cue

59:29.811 --> 59:31.563
He was fussing over the cello last time.

59:32.355 --> 59:34.024
Now, it's the violin?

59:34.941 --> 59:37.485
He doesn't like the piano or the cello.

59:37.486 --> 59:38.987
Can't seem to find what he likes.

59:40.530 --> 59:41.782
Maybe he doesn't like music?

59:43.700 --> 59:46.619
My Yun will become a musician.

59:46.620 --> 59:47.870
Don't say such things.

59:49.581 --> 59:51.290
You know it's not that easy.

59:55.837 --> 59:57.255
Let me buy this one for him.

59:57.881 --> 59:59.800
Tell him it's a gift from his uncle.

01:00:00.926 --> 01:00:02.969
Then, please buy this one for him.

01:00:03.720 --> 01:00:05.514
- We'll take this one.
- This one?

01:00:07.140 --> 01:00:09.934
Hold on… How much is it?

01:00:09.935 --> 01:00:11.311
I'll ring it right up for you.

01:00:12.145 --> 01:00:13.730
Thanks.

01:00:15.398 --> 01:00:17.149
DREAM INSTRUMENTS

01:00:17.150 --> 01:00:19.569
We can have dinner together
when Yun gets out of school.

01:00:21.029 --> 01:00:23.031
No. He has to go to his math academy.

01:00:24.574 --> 01:00:26.201
He attends an academy too?

01:00:28.954 --> 01:00:31.122
Right, as he should.

01:00:32.624 --> 01:00:35.168
He should. He's almost out
of elementary school now.

01:00:45.512 --> 01:00:47.138
Get back safely, Wan.

01:00:48.098 --> 01:00:50.183
Thanks. You too, Irang.

01:01:09.953 --> 01:01:12.204
HYEON'S GARDEN

01:01:12.205 --> 01:01:16.166
So, you're going to propose
to her again?

01:01:16.167 --> 01:01:18.879
You made a good point last time.

01:01:20.881 --> 01:01:22.256
I see.

01:01:22.257 --> 01:01:24.301
We could get new rings.

01:01:24.926 --> 01:01:26.760
A fresh proposal would be nice too.

01:01:26.761 --> 01:01:28.221
Huiju. Behind you.

01:01:28.763 --> 01:01:29.764
What?

01:01:45.864 --> 01:01:46.865
Did you hear that?

01:01:56.583 --> 01:01:59.586
Did you bring up the ring last night
because of the proposal?

01:02:03.173 --> 01:02:05.382
I mean, you know. It was more like…

01:02:05.383 --> 01:02:09.387
For a second there,
I thought you were suddenly into jewelry.

01:02:11.514 --> 01:02:13.475
You don't want to wear a wedding dress?

01:02:14.851 --> 01:02:15.852
Why bother?

01:02:18.355 --> 01:02:19.356
You know,

01:02:19.940 --> 01:02:21.941
you've been saying that a lot recently.

01:02:21.942 --> 01:02:24.151
But to say "why bother" about our wedding?

01:02:24.152 --> 01:02:25.570
There's no room for "why bother"s!

01:02:26.196 --> 01:02:29.031
But we already did all that.
Why would we do it again?

01:02:29.032 --> 01:02:30.574
But back then we were…

01:02:30.575 --> 01:02:32.452
That's when I started
having real feelings.

01:02:33.495 --> 01:02:34.496
What?

01:02:37.958 --> 01:02:39.501
I guess it wasn't the same for you.

01:02:44.798 --> 01:02:45.799
Babe…

01:02:46.716 --> 01:02:48.426
Hold on. Babe.

01:02:51.262 --> 01:02:53.765
Wait, you're saying
that's when you started?

01:02:55.266 --> 01:02:56.643
That late?

01:02:57.727 --> 01:03:00.479
We kissed and stuff way before then.

01:03:00.480 --> 01:03:01.982
When did you start?

01:03:03.733 --> 01:03:04.943
What?

01:03:33.596 --> 01:03:35.765
When did you start
having real feelings for me?
:cue

01:03:41.438 --> 01:03:42.439
From the start.

01:03:44.733 --> 01:03:45.734
You didn't know?

01:03:47.527 --> 01:03:49.446
I started liking you way back when.

01:03:50.405 --> 01:03:51.406
Way back when?

01:03:52.365 --> 01:03:54.951
Exactly how long ago is way back when?

01:03:55.827 --> 01:03:58.705
When you first told me your name.

01:03:59.706 --> 01:04:00.832
Who goes there?

01:04:04.169 --> 01:04:05.462
Your name.

01:04:06.546 --> 01:04:07.964
It is Seong Huiju.

01:04:10.800 --> 01:04:13.303
Back at that archery range?

01:04:16.347 --> 01:04:18.141
You were like a bright ember in the dark.

01:04:19.517 --> 01:04:20.685
I wanted to run after you.

01:04:22.645 --> 01:04:23.980
Since you were so popular,

01:04:24.981 --> 01:04:27.067
I kept hearing about you at school

01:04:28.109 --> 01:04:29.444
and even after graduation.

01:04:30.403 --> 01:04:32.906
I thought we'd run
into each other eventually,

01:04:34.449 --> 01:04:35.742
but it never happened.

01:04:36.409 --> 01:04:38.787
- Then, I saw you at…
- The Royal Birthday Banquet.

01:04:51.174 --> 01:04:53.551
You were just as bright an ember
that day.

01:04:56.888 --> 01:04:57.889
So you ran after me?

01:05:14.114 --> 01:05:15.115
Yeah.

01:05:16.116 --> 01:05:18.868
As fast as I could
because I was afraid of losing you.

01:05:35.135 --> 01:05:37.387
THE CROWN'S FINAL DUTY

01:06:34.152 --> 01:06:36.154
It was not mine when I wanted it.

01:06:38.031 --> 01:06:39.365
It was mine…

01:06:41.409 --> 01:06:42.492
when I did not want it.

01:06:45.330 --> 01:06:46.539
But in the end,

01:06:47.749 --> 01:06:49.000
it was my choice.

01:07:03.973 --> 01:07:04.974
I feel relieved.

01:07:22.283 --> 01:07:23.326
Babe!

01:07:25.745 --> 01:07:26.995
Sorry!

01:07:26.996 --> 01:07:29.999
I'm sorry. Work took forever.

01:07:30.625 --> 01:07:33.503
Are you done with the exhibit?
We can look at it some more.

01:07:35.713 --> 01:07:36.923
No, it's fine.

01:07:38.675 --> 01:07:39.926
Let's go.

01:07:40.510 --> 01:07:41.761
Let's go.

01:07:53.523 --> 01:07:55.983
:cue

01:07:55.984 --> 01:07:58.652
I'm going to eat this
in one bite.

01:07:58.653 --> 01:08:00.196
Wan, over here!

01:08:01.531 --> 01:08:03.073
Hurry up.

01:08:03.074 --> 01:08:04.075
Ms. Seong!

01:08:05.368 --> 01:08:06.369
Hmm.

01:08:08.121 --> 01:08:09.122
Let's wear them too.

01:08:10.039 --> 01:08:12.166
The jersey? You want to wear one?

01:08:12.750 --> 01:08:14.377
Yeah. I like jerseys.

01:08:17.005 --> 01:08:18.130
Let's go.

01:08:18.131 --> 01:08:19.756
-  Hi!
-  Let's go.

01:08:19.757 --> 01:08:22.176
Huh? Okay, let's go.

01:08:23.344 --> 01:08:24.469
ALL SEATS SOLD OUT

01:08:25.555 --> 01:08:26.597
It's starting.

01:08:29.767 --> 01:08:31.101
- I have one too.
- Like this?

01:08:36.399 --> 01:08:38.276
Castle Sharks! Yeah!

01:08:42.238 --> 01:08:43.363
Let's go!

01:08:46.784 --> 01:08:48.243
Are you kidding me right now?

01:08:48.244 --> 01:08:49.786
You must be joking!

01:08:49.787 --> 01:08:55.335
Shark attack! Let's go, Castle Sharks!

01:09:03.426 --> 01:09:04.552
Why am I not getting any?

01:09:05.261 --> 01:09:07.512
- What the…
- What?

01:09:07.513 --> 01:09:09.349
That's us!

01:09:09.849 --> 01:09:11.434
Us? Let's do it.

01:09:14.479 --> 01:09:18.940
Kiss! Kiss! Kiss!

01:09:18.941 --> 01:09:21.277
- Kiss!
- Kiss!

01:09:21.861 --> 01:09:22.862
Sorry.

01:09:24.655 --> 01:09:25.823
Should we speed things up?

01:09:29.243 --> 01:09:30.912
We don't need to maintain decorum now?

01:09:31.496 --> 01:09:33.289
Yeah. No more decorum.

01:09:59.023 --> 01:10:03.277
One more time!
One more time!

01:10:04.529 --> 01:10:06.571
- One more time!
- One more time!

01:10:07.657 --> 01:10:10.576
PERFECT CROWN

01:11:55.890 --> 01:11:57.974
Translated by Justin S. Kim

01:11:57.975 --> 01:12:01.687
PERFECT CROWN
